Commentary Text: Ashwin to Rahane, out Lbw!! Ashwin breaks the partnership. Rahane and Conway have a discussion regarding the review, but looks like the former himself didn't want to send it upstairs. Carrom ball and Rahane premeditated the sweep, the length was too full and he ended up playing all over it, struck low on the pad and right in front of the stumps. That would have crashed into leg-stump and umpire Vinod Seshan made the right call. Rahane lbw b Ashwin 31(19) [4s-2 6s-1]
